  "dateModified": "2026-03-03",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "The structural subject-position produced when platforms industrialize the confessional incitement-to-discourse, turning every user into a performer of expertise whose intellectual labor is governed by anxiety, feeling rules, and platform-native logics of visibility. The position is *platformal* rather than *platformed*: the platform is not a tool the intellectual uses but the structural condition that produces the intellectual's mode of intellectuality. They think in threads, evaluate ideas by engagement, produce analysis in platform-native formats. The condition becomes sharpest under crisis, when the intellectual is incited to perform continued expertise on ideas about which they are themselves naive — and the platform's feeling rules format partial understanding as complete understanding.",
  "name": "Neurotic platformal intellectual",
